 Nation at a Glance

 Couple dies on debt pyre

 ChalakKudy (PTI): A debt-ridden farmer and his wife ended their lives by jumping into a funeral pyre they built in the compound of their house in Kerala, police said.

 Gopan (44), a former theatre actor from Thrissur in northern Kerala, and his wife took the extreme step after the Plantation Corporation of India, which had leased out some land to them, demanded it back after expiry of the lease, police sources added.

 Their son saw the fire and found his parents engulfed in flames. Alerted by his cries, neighbours rushed in to help but the woman died on the pyre. Gopan succumbed to injuries at the hospital.

 Sandal flies at Sudarshan

 Sholapur (PTI): A person threw a sandal 

 at RSS chief K.S. Sudarshan after he unveiled a statue of 

 Chhatrapati Shivaji here on Thursday, police sources said.

 A number of organisations, including the Maratha Seva Sangh, Sambhaji Brigade and the Vidrohi Sanskrutik Chalwal, were opposed to the unveiling of the statue by the RSS chief.

 The police had earlier detained nearly 40 people to prevent trouble. An unidentified person from the gathering hurled the sandal at Sudarshan, the sources said.

 An RSS worker later registered a complaint at Fauzdar Chowdi police station. No arrest has been made so far.

 Lakhs looted

 Jalandhar (PTI): Three armed men looted over Rs 63 lakh from a branch of UCO bank on Friday, minutes after it reopened after the lunch break. 

 The trio, with their faces covered, snatched the guards gun before entering the managers cabin. Holding him at gun point, they snatched the keys of the strong room and decamped with Rs 63,20,120.

 Vigilance week

 Calcutta : Vigilance Awareness Week, 

 being observed by the Employees State Insurance Corporation 

 (ESI), came to a close on Thursday. The programme, organised 

 at the behest of the Central Vigilance Commission, started 

 on Monday with the staff of ESI corporation taking a pledge 

 to eradicate corruption.

 VIP son blow

 New Delhi (PTI): A court has rejected 

 the bail plea of Vikas Yadav, son of former Rajya Sabha 

 MP D.P. Yadav, facing trial in the Nitish Katara murder 

 case.

 An Australian national aboard a Quantas Airlines flight from Mumbai to Sydney was disembarked after a row over seat allotments. The flight returned to Mumbai to offload the passenger.




